tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE GeneticsData (id INT PRIMARY KEY,
source_name VARCHAR(50),
source_type VARCHAR(50),
chromosome VARCHAR(10),
position INT,
variant_type VARCHAR(10),
gene_name VARCHAR(50),
allele_frequency FLOAT)

CREATE TABLE variations (
    variation_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    gene_id INT NOT NULL,
    variation_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    variation_type VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    CONSTRAINT fk_gene_id FOREIGN KEY (gene_id) REFERENCES genes(gene_id)
);

CREATE TABLE SampleData (
  sample_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  sample_name VARCHAR(255),
  genetic_data TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE SourceAData (
  sourceA_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  sample_id UUID REFERENCES SampleData(sample_id),
  sourceA_info TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE SourceBData (
  sourceB_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  sample_id UUID REFERENCES SampleData(sample_id),
  sourceB_info TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE gene_info (
  gene_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  gene_name VARCHAR(255),
  chromosome VARCHAR(10),
  start_position INT,
  end_position INT
)

CREATE TABLE gene_expression (
  sample_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  gene_id INT,
  expression_level FLOAT,
  assay_type VARCHAR(50),
  FOREIGN KEY (gene_id) REFERENCES gene_info(gene_id)
)

CREATE TABLE gene_variants (
  variant_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  gene_id INT,
  variant_type VARCHAR(50),
  variant_position INT,
  FOREIGN KEY (gene_id) REFERENCES gene_info(gene_id)
)

CREATE TABLE gene_annotations (
  annotation_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  gene_id INT,
  annotation_text TEXT,
  annotation_source VARCHAR(255),
  FOREIGN KEY (gene_id) REFERENCES gene_info(gene_id)
)

CREATE TABLE gene_interactions (
  interaction_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  gene_id_1 INT,
  gene_id_2 INT,
  interaction_type VARCHAR(50),
  FOREIGN KEY (gene_id_1) REFERENCES gene_info(gene_id),
  FOREIGN KEY (gene_id_2) REFERENCES gene_info(gene_id)
)
